# Docker Workflow

## Core Principle

All commands run inside Docker containers. Never install project dependencies (Node, Python, npm packages, pip packages) directly on the host machine.

## Development

```bash
# Start dev server with hot-reload
docker compose up

# Access at http://localhost:5173
```

## Testing

```bash
# Unit tests (Vitest)
docker compose --profile test run --rm test-unit

# E2E tests (pytest + Playwright)
docker compose --profile test run --rm test-e2e

# Run tests for a specific SRS requirement
docker compose --profile test run --rm test-e2e pytest -m fr1 -v
```

## Production Build

```bash
docker build -t fav-pkmn .
docker run -p 8080:80 fav-pkmn
# Access at http://localhost:8080
```

## Key Details

- The `app` service uses a bind-mount for source files so Vite HMR works
- An anonymous volume at `/app/node_modules` prevents host OS conflicts
- The `test-e2e` service depends on `app` and connects via the Docker network
- Use `docker compose down` to stop all services
